http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/National-baseball-championship-begins/article14023867.ece

The four-day 30th Senior National Baseball Championship for Men and Women began here on Wednesday with 24 men’s and 19 women’s teams from 24 States taking part.The event also prompted vice-chairman of Baseball Association of Karnataka B.L. Vedmurthy to announce the launch of an IPL series on the lines of cricket soon.As many as 18 teams will be formed across the country under the new series to begin with.The championship has been organised by the Baseball Association of Karnataka (BAK) under the auspices of Amateur Baseball Federation of India, which was recognised by the Union Ministry of Youth and Affairs and Indian Olympic Association affiliated to the International Baseball Federation of Asia.